</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/udevictionmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DevictionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#628CBC>(8/16/02 10:57:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A New Mage</span><hr size=1> welcome to the club. )  I think I can safely say most mages I've talked to are genuinely nice people..so feel free to bother us ingame with any questions you have.  My friends list is about 1/3rd new mages that have asked me for help from 7 zones away.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for your questions...<br>
<br>
anything and everything you'll need to know about magelife is here:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
But just off the cuff..<br>
<br>
Earth pets have the most HPs of your 4 elementals.  But they have very low agi, so most of the time they are being hit with alot of damage.  Casts root spell.<br>
<br>
Water has the second most hp, and does nice dmg with a dd spell.  I'm fond of this guy.<br>
<br>
Air has the 3rd amount of hp, can cast a very short duration (couple seconds) stun spell, and casts invis on itself when not in melee.  (The invis is more hassle then its worth now, as pets are indifferent to mobs if they aren't on a mobs hate list).<br>
<br>
Fire has the lowest hps (roughly half of the earth pet), casts an irresistable damage shield on itself (level+1 pts of dmg/better than your DS) and a DD spell (level+2 pts of dmg).  With certain low hp mobs, this pet can annihilate them.<br>
<br>
Your elemental pets used to have high resists/immunties to specfic things like poison, fire, magic, etc.  However VI has changed it recently and the Mage community is still trying to figure out wtf is going on.  Alot of knowledge that was taken as truth and for granted is now gone concerning this.<br>
<br>
Your monster summoning line is pretty vanilla.  Yes it will cast some spells, but overall it's ment to be your average tank with decent hps and decent damage.  Alot of mages in the mid-higher levels prefer this pet for soloing in situations.<br>
<br>
Your manapool's foundation is INT.  Start there.<br>
<br>
Don't bother with buying all your pet spells early on in your walk.  Water pet is the best to solo with period.  You'll have plenty of opportunity to fiddle around with the other pets.  But if you're truly concerned with saving pp..sense summoned, true north, most of the [ summon crappy 2hb staffs ] I've never ever used.<br>
<br>
And finally here's what I always tell new mages:<br>
<br>
Tank for your pet.  Keeps him alive longer and gets your defense skill up.  Don't forget to research Dodge at 16 (i think...may be 12).  if you hunt orcs (gfay for ex.) You can give your pets weapons.  Rusty 2hs longswords are good for your pets. )<br>
<br>
Enjoy. )<br>
<br>
